bonds are shown to be effective in immunizing surplus over short and
long horizons. Delta gamma hedging is generally only effective over
short horizons. The results of the paper have implications for how
providers of post retirement income benefit streams can manage risks in
demanding conditions where innovation in investment markets can support
new products and increase the product range.},
