gher in Norway in the lower to middle part of the income distribution in both men and women. Conclusions and Relevance In Norway, there were substantial and increasing gaps in life expectancy by income level from 2005 to 2015. The largest differences in life expectancy between Norway and United States were for individuals in the lower to middle part of the income distribution.},
